The client in consultation with lead auditor and auditee organization make the final decisions on which OH & S system elements, physical locations and organizational activities are to be audited within a specified time frame. The scope and depth of the audit should be designed to meet the client’s specific information needs. Generally the audit is carried out to cover the following aspects:
a) Identification of areas of OH & S system, which require improvement;
b) Assessment of effectiveness of measures taken for controlling the hazards;
c) Recommendation of measures to strengthen the OH & S system;

